Practical 05 :- To demonstrate the use of internal and external CSS to style a web page 
 
Internal css 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
    <title>Internal CSS Lab Practical</title> 
    <style> 
        body { 
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
            background-color: blanchedalmond; 
            padding: 40px; 
        } 
        .card { 
            background-color: #ffffff; 
            border: 2px solid #007bff; 
            border-radius: 10px; 
            padding: 20px; 
            max-width: 500px; 
            margin: auto;  
        } 
        h1 { 
            color: #007bff; 
            text-align: center; 
        } 
        p { 
            color: #333333; 
            line-height: 1.6; 
            font-size: 16px; 
        } 
    </style> 
</head> 
<body> 
    <div class="card"> 
        <h1>Welcome to Web Design</h1> 
        <p>This webpage demonstrates how internal CSS can be used to 
improve the appearance of HTML elements.</p> 
        <p>By defining styles inside the style section, you can control 
the colors, spacing, and layout of the page.</p> 
        <p>Internal CSS helps create a clean and attractive design while 
keeping all styling rules in one place.</p> 
    </div> 
</body> 
</html>

