External css 
Style.css 
.container { 
  background-color: white; 
  width: 400px; 
  margin: 50px auto; 
  padding: 20px; 
  border: 2px solid black; 
} 
h1 { 
  color: blue; 
  text-align: center; 
} 
.action-btn { 
  background-color: blue; 
  color: white; 
  padding: 10px 20px; 
} 
 
External.html 
<html> 
  <head> 
    <title>Basic External CSS</title> 
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" /> 
  </head> 
  <body> 
    <div class="container"> 
      <h1>Welcome to Styling</h1> 
      <p>This page demonstrates how an external CSS file can style HTML 
elements neatly and consistently.</p> 
      <button class="action-btn">Learn More</button> 
    </div> 
</body> </html>
